column5: My wife and I returned last evening from our annual week at Fisherman's Cove. We had a great time with cooperative weather and cooperative walleye's. We didn't catch any big sows. However, we did catch more in the low to mid 20's than we ever have in the past. Most of the fish were on sharp break in rocks. We didn't have much luck on sand. The boat worked perfectly and we avoided all the rocks. The countdown is on for 2013.
